---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="Turning Raw Claims into Revenue-Ready Assets | Case Study">
  <div class="case-bg">
    <div class="case-shell">
      <a href="/case-studies" class="back-button">&larr; Back to Case Studies</a>

      <header class="case-header">
        <span class="case-eyebrow">FOUNDATION CASE STUDY &middot; DE-IDENTIFICATION</span>
        <h1>Turning Raw Pharmacy Claims into Revenue-Ready Assets</h1>
        <p class="case-lede">
          The de-identification layer underneath the platform &mdash; the system that takes
          billions of raw NCPDP transaction records and produces clean, HIPAA-compliant
          datasets that the rest of the monetization pipeline can build on.
        </p>
        <div class="case-meta">
          <div class="meta-block"><span class="meta-key">ROLE</span><span class="meta-val">Architect &amp; builder</span></div>
          <div class="meta-block"><span class="meta-key">SCALE</span><span class="meta-val">Billions of claims, daily +&nbsp;historical</span></div>
          <div class="meta-block"><span class="meta-key">STACK</span><span class="meta-val">Snowflake, SQL, Tasks, Python</span></div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="case-section">
        <h2>The problem</h2>
        <p>
          Raw upstream claims data sat in a transaction log table that nobody downstream could touch.
          PHI everywhere, NCPDP fields inconsistent across source systems, and no audit trail to satisfy
          expert determination requirements. Without a transformation layer that produced clean,
          de-identified datasets, none of the platform's downstream monetization was possible.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="case-section">
        <h2>What I built</h2>

        <div class="block-grid">
          <div class="block">
            <h3>Parameterized de-id stored procedures</h3>
            <p>Snowflake stored procs that transform raw transaction logs into NCPDP-aligned, de-identified records following the project's expert determination ruleset. Same code path runs daily and historical.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="block">
            <h3>Daily + on-demand orchestration</h3>
            <p>Snowflake tasks run the daily increment automatically; the same procedures run unchanged for multi-year historical backfills when onboarding a new client or correcting upstream data.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="block">
            <h3>Audit-ready metadata</h3>
            <p>Every run logs row counts, transformation rules applied, and validation outcomes. Auditors can trace any record back to the rule that produced it &mdash; required for ED defense and client compliance reviews.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="block">
            <h3>Validated outputs by design</h3>
            <p>Validation queries run inline with each load. Records that fail compliance rules get routed to a quarantine path; clean records flow through to tokenization.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="block">
            <h3>Schema designed for joins downstream</h3>
            <p>The output table (TRANSACTION_DEID) is the join surface for every client feed downstream. Column ordering, naming, and clustering keys were chosen with the V2 tokenization rebuild in mind well before V2 happened.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="block">
            <h3>Cross-team coordination</h3>
            <p>Worked directly with data science and analytics on which upstream fields were valid, with legal on the ED ruleset, and with downstream consumers on output schema. Shipped the layer with sign-off from all three.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="case-section">
        <h2>Why it matters</h2>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li>This is the layer the entire $9M ARR product sits on. If de-id breaks, no client gets data that day.</li>
          <li>Same pipeline supports daily delivery and full historical backfills &mdash; one code path, not two.</li>
          <li>Audit trail and ED-defensible rules let RedSail extend the platform to new buyer types without re-architecting compliance.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <div class="case-footer">
        <p>Want to talk about this layer or how it slots into the broader platform?</p>
        <div class="footer-buttons">
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-ruffin-a9b767102" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="footer-cta">Connect on LinkedIn</a>
          <a href="/case-studies" class="footer-link">See more case studies &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .case-bg {
      min-height: 100vh;
      background: var(--background-color);
      color: var(--text-color);
      padding: 100px 20px 80px;
    }
    .case-shell {
      max-width: 880px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .back-button {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--primary-color);
      text-decoration: none;
      transition: opacity 0.3s;
    }
    .back-button:hover { opacity: 0.7; }

    .case-header { margin-bottom: 4rem; }
    .case-eyebrow {
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.15em;
      color: var(--primary-color);
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }
    .case-header h1 {
      font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1.15;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #ffffff 0%, #c8b8e8 100%);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      background-clip: text;
    }
    .case-lede {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      font-weight: 300;
    }
    .case-meta {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 16px;
      padding: 20px;
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
      border-radius: 12px;
    }
    .meta-block { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
    .meta-key { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--primary-color); text-transform: uppercase; }
    .meta-val { font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--text-color); font-weight: 500; }

    .case-section { margin-bottom: 3.5rem; }
    .case-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.35rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text-color);
      margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      padding-bottom: 8px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--card-border);
    }
    .case-section p { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .bullets { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
    .bullets li {
      padding: 10px 0 10px 22px;
      position: relative;
      font-size: 0.97rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .bullets li::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      top: 18px;
      width: 6px;
      height: 6px;
      background: var(--primary-color);
      border-radius: 50%;
    }

    .block-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 16px; }
    .block {
      padding: 22px;
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      transition: border-color 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
    }
    .block:hover { border-color: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.3); box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.06); }
    .block h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-color); margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .block p { font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }

    .case-footer {
      margin-top: 4rem;
      padding: 32px;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.04) 0%, rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.08) 100%);
      border: 1px solid rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.18);
      border-radius: 14px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .case-footer p { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.4rem; }
    .footer-buttons { display: flex; gap: 14px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; }
    .footer-cta {
      padding: 0.85rem 2rem;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #a855f7 0%, #7c3aed 100%);
      color: white;
      border-radius: 10px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      transition: all 0.3s;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 24px var(--primary-glow);
    }
    .footer-cta:hover { transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 8px 40px rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.5); }
    .footer-link { color: var(--primary-color); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 500; }
    .footer-link:hover { opacity: 0.7; }

    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      .case-meta { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .block-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
  </style>
</MainLayout>
